mitre_attack_techniques.signature_description: Adversaries may attempt to dump credentials to obtain account login and credential material, normally in the form of a hash or a clear text password, from the operating system and software.
An adversary may steal web application or service session cookies and use them to gain access to web applications or Internet services as an authenticated user without needing credentials.
Adversaries may search for common password storage locations to obtain user credentials.
Adversaries may search compromised systems to find and obtain insecurely stored credentials.
Adversaries may acquire credentials from web browsers by reading files specific to the target browser.
Adversaries may search local file systems and remote file shares for files containing insecurely stored credentials.
An adversary may attempt to get detailed information about the operating system and hardware, including version, patches, hotfixes, service packs, and architecture.
Adversaries may attempt to get information about running processes on a system.
Adversaries may interact with the Windows Registry to gather information about the system, configuration, and installed software.
Adversaries may attempt to get a listing of software and software versions that are installed on a system or in a cloud environment.
Adversaries may communicate using application layer protocols to avoid detection/network filtering by blending in with existing traffic.

An adversary may use legitimate desktop support and remote access software, such as Team Viewer, AnyDesk, Go2Assist, LogMein, AmmyyAdmin, etc, to establish an interactive command and control channel to target systems within networks.
Adversaries may interact with the native OS application programming interface (API) to execute behaviors.
Adversaries may search local system sources, such as file systems and configuration files or local databases, to find files of interest and sensitive data prior to Exfiltration.
Adversaries may attempt to manipulate features of their artifacts to make them appear legitimate or benign to users and/or security tools.
Adversaries may circumvent mechanisms designed to control elevate privileges to gain higher-level permissions.
Adversaries may destroy data and files on specific systems or in large numbers on a network to interrupt availability to systems, services, and network resources.

signature_matches.name: access .NET resource
signature_matches.description: executable/resource
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: access .NET resource
    namespace: executable/resource
    authors:
      - "@mr-tz"
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: thread
    examples:
      - 387f15043f0198fd3a637b0758c2b6dde9ead795c3ed70803426fc355731b173:0x06000084
  features:
    - and:
      - format: dotnet
      - or:
        - api: System.Resources.ResourceManager::ctor
        - api: System.Reflection.Assembly::GetManifestResourceStream

signature_matches.name: generate method via reflection in .NET
signature_matches.description: load-code/dotnet : https://github.com/bohops/DynamicDotNet/blob/main/assembly_loader/DynamicAssemblyLoader.cs
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: generate method via reflection in .NET
    namespace: load-code/dotnet
    authors:
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    description: https://github.com/bohops/DynamicDotNet/blob/main/assembly_loader/DynamicAssemblyLoader.cs
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: call
  features:
    - or:
      - api: System.Reflection.Emit.DynamicMethod::ctor
      - api: System.Reflection.Emit.DynamicMethod::GetILGenerator
      - api: System.Reflection.Emit.ILGenerator::Emit
      - api: System.Reflection.Emit.ILGenerator::EmitCall
      - api: System.Reflection.Emit.ILGenerator::EmitCalli
      - api: System.Reflection.Emit.ILGenerator::EmitWriteLine

signature_matches.name: contain loop
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: contain loop
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
    lib: true
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: unsupported  # requires characteristic features
    examples:
      - 08AC667C65D36D6542917655571E61C8:0x406EAA
  features:
    - or:
      - characteristic: loop
      - characteristic: tight loop
      - characteristic: recursive call

signature_matches.name: generate random numbers in .NET
signature_matches.description: data-manipulation/prng
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: generate random numbers in .NET
    namespace: data-manipulation/prng
    authors:
      - anushka.virgaonkar@mandiant.com
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: function

signature_matches.name: reference analysis tools strings
signature_matches.description: anti-analysis

    name: reference analysis tools strings
    namespace: anti-analysis
    authors:
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    scopes:

      dynamic: file
    mbc:
